In the past few weeks, UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson has faced anger from the public for allegedly holding parties when the country was under COVID-19 lockdowns. However, Johnson and his cabinet have for the moment sidetracked the issue by suggesting that the government could abolish the BBC license fee in 2027. Some political experts say this is a typical example of a cornered British politician trying to divert attention. In this episode of #BizBeat, CGTN's Aaron Liu explains.